            <p>Two brokers: one charges 0.8 pips on EUR/USD, another charges 1.5 pips. Seems small. But if you're trading 5 times a day at 1 lot, that 0.7 pip difference adds up to about <strong>$8,750 per year</strong>. That's before swap rates and withdrawal fees.</p>

