            <p>Some brokers advertise 0.0 spreads but slip your entries by 2 pips when markets move fast. Others show 0.8 spreads and fill you instantly at quoted prices. The "cheap" broker often costs more when you're actually trading. We test execution during volatile sessions before recommending anyone.</p>

